GoogleTypeDate.description: Represents a whole or partial calendar date, such as a birthday. The time of day and time zone are either specified elsewhere or are insignificant. The date is relative to the Gregorian Calendar. This can represent one of the following: * A full date, with non-zero year, month, and day values. * A month and day, with a zero year (for example, an anniversary). * A year on its own, with a zero month and a zero day. * A year and month, with a zero day (for example, a credit card expiration date). Related types: * google.type.TimeOfDay * google.type.DateTime * google.protobuf.Timestamp

year.description: Year of the date. Must be from 1 to 9999, or 0 to specify a date without a year.

day.description: Day of a month. Must be from 1 to 31 and valid for the year and month, or 0 to specify a year by itself or a year and month where the day isn't significant.

month.description: Month of a year. Must be from 1 to 12, or 0 to specify a year without a month and day.

additionalProperties.description: Properties of the object. Contains field @type with type URL.

details.description: A list of messages that carry the error details. There is a common set of message types for APIs to use.

message.description: A developer-facing error message, which should be in English. Any user-facing error message should be localized and sent in the google.rpc.Status.details field, or localized by the client.

code.description: The status code, which should be an enum value of google.rpc.Code.

GoogleRpcStatus.description: The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is used by [gRPC](https://github.com/grpc). Each `Status` message contains three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details. You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the [API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors).

networkStatusReport.description: Output only. Network specs collected periodically.

batteryStatusReport.description: Output only. Battery reports collected periodically.

graphicsInfo.description: Output only. Contains information regarding Graphic peripherals for the device.

peripheralsReport.description: Output only. Peripherals reports collected periodically sorted in a decreasing order of report_time.

cpuStatusReport.description: Output only. CPU status reports collected periodically sorted in a decreasing order of report_time.

name.description: Output only. Resource name of the device.

orgUnitId.description: Output only. Organization unit ID of the device.

customer.description: Output only. Google Workspace Customer whose enterprise enrolled the device.

storageInfo.description: Output only. Information of storage specs for the device.

storageStatusReport.description: Output only. Storage reports collected periodically.

audioStatusReport.description: Output only. Audio reports collected periodically sorted in a decreasing order of report_time.

serialNumber.description: Output only. Device serial number. This value is the same as the Admin Console's Serial Number in the ChromeOS Devices tab.

memoryInfo.description: Output only. Information regarding memory specs for the device.

cpuInfo.description: Output only. Information regarding CPU specs for the device.

GoogleChromeManagementV1CountInstalledAp.description: Response containing details of queried installed apps.

installedApps.description: List of installed apps matching request.

nextPageToken.description: Token to specify the next page of the request.

totalSize.description: Total number of installed apps matching request.

mdn.description: Output only. The mobile directory number associated with the device's sim card.

macAddress.description: Output only. MAC address (if applicable) of the corresponding network device.

imei.description: Output only. IMEI (if applicable) of the corresponding network device.

meid.description: Output only. MEID (if applicable) of the corresponding network device.

iccid.description: Output only. The integrated circuit card ID associated with the device's sim card.

GoogleChromeManagementV1NetworkDevice.description: Details about the network device. * This field provides device information, which is static and will not change over time. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportNetworkDeviceConfiguration](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportNetworkDeviceConfiguration) * Data Collection Frequency: At device startup * Default Data Reporting Frequency: At device startup - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: Yes * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

GoogleChromeManagementV1AudioStatusRepor.description: Status data for storage. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceAudioStatus](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceAudioStatus) * Data Collection Frequency: 10 minutes * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

inputMute.description: Output only. Is active input device mute or not.

outputMute.description: Output only. Is active output device mute or not.

inputDevice.description: Output only. Active input device's name.

inputGain.description: Output only. Active input device's gain in [0, 100].

outputDevice.description: Output only. Active output device's name.

reportTime.description: Output only. Timestamp of when the sample was collected on device.

outputVolume.description: Output only. Active output device's volume in [0, 100].

adapter.description: Output only. Adapter name. Example: Mesa DRI Intel(R) UHD Graphics 620 (Kabylake GT2).

deviceId.description: Output only. Represents the graphics card device id.

driverVersion.description: Output only. Version of the GPU driver.

cpuReports.description: The DeviceHardwareCountReport for device cpu type (for example Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-10610U CPU @ 1.80GHz).

modelReports.description: The DeviceHardwareCountReport for device model type (for example Acer C7 Chromebook).

memoryReports.description: The DeviceHardwareCountReport for device memory amount in gigabytes (for example 16).

storageReports.description: The DeviceHardwareCountReport for device storage amount in gigabytes (for example 128).

GoogleChromeManagementV1CountChromeHardw.description: Response containing a list of devices with a specific type of hardware specification from the requested hardware type.

temperatureCelsius.description: Output only. CPU temperature in Celsius.

label.description: Output only. CPU label. Example: Core 0

GoogleChromeManagementV1CpuTemperatureIn.description: CPU temperature of a device. Sampled per CPU core in Celsius. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceCpuInfo](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceCpuInfo) * Data Collection Frequency: Every 10 minutes * Default Data Reporting Frequency: 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

GoogleChromeManagementV1PrinterReport.description: Report for CountPrintJobsByPrinter, contains statistics on printer usage. Contains the total number of print jobs initiated with this printer, the number of users and the number of devices that have initiated at least one print job with this printer.

jobCount.description: Number of print jobs sent to the printer.

deviceCount.description: Number of chrome devices that have been used to send print jobs to the specified printer.

userCount.description: Number of users that have sent print jobs to the printer.

chromeAppInfo.description: Output only. Chrome Web Store app information.

reviewRating.description: Output only. The rating of the app (on 5 stars). Chrome Web Store review information will always be for the latest version of an app.

iconUri.description: Output only. A link to an image that can be used as an icon for the product.

appId.description: Output only. Unique store identifier for the item. Examples: "gmbmikajjgmnabiglmofipeabaddhgne" for the Save to Google Drive Chrome extension, "com.google.android.apps.docs" for the Google Drive Android app.

revisionId.description: Output only. App version. A new revision is committed whenever a new version of the app is published.

homepageUri.description: Output only. Home page or Website uri.

privacyPolicyUri.description: Output only. The URI pointing to the privacy policy of the app, if it was provided by the developer. Version-specific field that will only be set when the requested app version is found.

serviceError.description: Output only. Information about a partial service error if applicable.

publisher.description: Output only. The publisher of the item.

isPaidApp.description: Output only. Indicates if the app has to be paid for OR has paid content.

reviewNumber.description: Output only. Number of reviews received. Chrome Web Store review information will always be for the latest version of an app.

detailUri.description: Output only. The uri for the detail page of the item.

GoogleChromeManagementV1DeviceHardwareCo.description: Report for CountChromeDevicesPerHardwareSpecResponse, contains the count of devices with a unique hardware specification.

bucket.description: Public name of the hardware specification.

count.description: Count of devices with a unique hardware specification.

telemetryUsers.description: Telemetry users returned in the response.

nextPageToken.description: Token to specify next page in the list.

GoogleChromeManagementV1ListTelemetryUse.description: Response message for listing telemetry users for a customer.

totalRamBytes.description: Output only. Total RAM in bytes.

availableRamBytes.description: Output only. Amount of available RAM in bytes.

totalMemoryEncryption.description: Output only. Total memory encryption info for the device.

GoogleChromeManagementV1MemoryInfo.description: Memory information of a device. * This field has both telemetry and device information: - `totalRamBytes` - Device information - `availableRamBytes` - Telemetry information - `totalMemoryEncryption` - Device information * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceMemoryInfo](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceMemoryInfo) * Data Collection Frequency: - `totalRamBytes` - Only at upload - `availableRamBytes` - Every 10 minutes - `totalMemoryEncryption` - at device startup * Default Data Reporting Frequency: - `totalRamBytes` - 3 hours - `availableRamBytes` - 3 hours - `totalMemoryEncryption` - at device startup - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: only for `totalMemoryEncryption` * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A

systemRamFreeBytes.description: Output only. Amount of free RAM in bytes (unreliable due to Garbage Collection).

reportTime.description: Output only. The timestamp in milliseconds representing time at which this report was sampled.

pageFaults.description: Output only. Number of page faults during this collection

sampleFrequency.description: Output only. Frequency the report is sampled.

GoogleChromeManagementV1MemoryStatusRepo.description: Contains samples of memory status reports. * This field is telemetry information and this will change over time as the device is utilized. * Data for this field is controlled via policy: [ReportDeviceMemoryInfo](https://chromeenterprise.google/policies/#ReportDeviceMemoryInfo) * Data Collection Frequency: Only at upload, SystemRamFreeByes is collected every 10 minutes * Default Data Reporting Frequency: Every 3 hours - Policy Controlled: Yes * Cache: If the device is offline, the collected data is stored locally, and will be reported when the device is next online: No * Reported for affiliated users only: N/A
